      • computeMetadata

        private void computeMetadata(java.util.List<OntStateChangeBuf> stateChanges)
                      throws org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException
        Method computes all metadata (aggregation components) of the input discrete state changes. Via iteration over the input state change list, the metadata are collected like the quantity for each individual state value. More metadata should be implemented here if it based on the state changes explicitly.
        Parameters:
        stateChanges - are the state changes to compute the aggregated metadata.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException - is thrown in case the state change could not be transformed into a string.

      • computeAggregatedMetadata

        private void computeAggregatedMetadata(java.util.List<OntAggregatedStateChange> stateChanges)
                                throws org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException
        Method computes all metadata (aggregation components) of the input aggregated, discrete state changes. Via iteration over the input state change list, the metadata are collected like the quantity for each individual state value. More metadata should be implemented here if it based on aggregated state changes explicitly.
        Parameters:
        stateChanges - are the aggregated state changes, which should be aggregated again.
        Throws:
        org.openbase.jul.exception.NotAvailableException - is thrown in case the state change could not be transformed into a string.

        Parameters:
